body:
It would be nice to "always" force a facet refinement without being able to clear it from the UI. Meaning the default "state" would be with the forced facet value so it's not considered "filtered" yet by the UI and thus the "clear all" widget wouldn't allow to clear this "forced" value.

Here is an use case: say I have some products each with a "brand" and a "color" attributes. I want a "global" search page with instant search which allows the user to control both brand & color facets refinements. But I also want a dedicated page for each brand and with only the color facet, and a dedicated page for each color and with only the brand facet.

In my case it's not an option to create an index for each possibility since in the real world I have much more attributes than just "brand" and "color" (without mentioning an index for each locale) and I want to have a dedicated page for each attribute (dynamically).

For now the only possibility I have with the library is the following:

``` javascript
// For the "Apple" brand dedicated page for instance

const search = instantsearch({
    // ...
    searchParameters: {
        disjunctiveFacets: ['brand']
    }
});

search.addWidget({
    init: function(args) {
        args.helper.addDisjunctiveFacetRefinement('brand', 'Apple');
    }
});

search.addWidget(instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({
    container: '#color',
    attributeName: 'color',
    operator: 'or'
}));

search.start();
```

Is there some undocumented black magic solution I'm not aware of? Otherwise, would you consider such behavior in the lib? ;-)

Thanks.
